{"key":"post-18943865","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>18943865</id>\n<content>Two things:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;First, don't use aluminum trays.&amp;nbsp; The mycelium eats holes in it, and then pins on the bottom from the fresh air.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Second, simply pour water over the top of the substrate and around the edges, wait an hour for it to absorb, and then pour whatever hasn't absorbed back out.&amp;nbsp; You could do the whole thing with a lot of misting, but this is easier and faster.&lt;br /&gt;RR&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is after one flush:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/files/07-45/456009399-Aluminum_shiitake_tray.jpg&quot; class=&quot;highslide&quot; onclick=&quot;return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;/forums/thumbs/07-45/456009399-thumb_Aluminum_shiitake_tray.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>18943887</next>\n<prev>18943860</prev>\n<first>18943831</first>\n<last>18948052</last>\n<when>1381159392</when>\n<utime>10/07/13 06:23 PM</utime>\n</post>"}